summary: Pokemon Card of the Day #1473: Sawsbuck (Black & White)
title: Pokemon Card of the Day #1473: Sawsbuck (Black & White)
body:
Sawsbuck was yet another Grass-type in the Black & White set that could heal itself, but that wasn’t the draw this time. Getting stronger with more Grass Energy on the field was what you’d be looking for. Sure, the damage was slow to build, but at least it was something to look at, right?

90 HP was pretty normal for a Stage 1. It was high enough to handle early HGSS-On attackers like Yanmega and Tornadus, at least, but Reshiram and Zekrom as well as the many Pokemon EX later on as well as in the BLW-On format just plowed through this. The Fire Weakness wasn’t all that big since the top Fire-types could KO anyway. The Water Resistance was at least something useful for earlier formats seeing some Kingdra and Vanilluxe. Being able to retreat for a single Energy was quite nice indeed even if Sawsbuck wasn’t the bulkiest thing out there.

Nature Power started off slow. 20 damage for a Colorless Energy was nothing to write home about. The attack gained 10 more for each Grass Energy attached to Pokemon on both sides of play, so it could go up by quite a bit. Sadly, Grass was not a very big type while Sawsbuck was available, so it was going to rely almost exclusively on its own side. It did, theoretically, have some use in Meganium Prime decks since those wanted to stack Energy. There were better attackers for it, but at least Sawsbuck could hit pretty hard later in a game.

Horn Leech was going to do a consistent 60 damage and heal 20 off of Sawsbuck, but that wasn’t even close to good enough for a Grass and 2 Colorless Energy. The attack was a few years too late to be notable.

Sawsbuck never had a good chance to shine. The format was not the most friendly to Pokemon that required Grass Energy, and any really quick deck, especially ones based around Pokemon EX, just overwhelmed any strategy Sawsbuck could be used in. The best Grass-types at the time, such as Yanmega and Accelgor, used Colorless Energy or no Energy at all. This left Sawsbuck as just an afterthought that might have been better at another time. Sceptile from Great Encounters and Meganium from Neo Genesis would have been awesome with this if they were available.

title: Wild Scizor encounter idea
body:
(A sort of special event catch like Sudowoodo and Snorlax basically).

A monster has been scaring people in a mine. In truth a scyther got stuck in the mine and evolved into a scizor due to all the surrounding minerals.

*I am dissapointed by Scizor as a scyther evolution because it lacks reptilian features but I think this would be cool.

blog.name: friendsafariserver
blog.title: Friend Safari!
blog.description:
Friend Safari is a SFW, OC-friendly, paragraph-style roleplay server for main series Pokémon games. From Kanto to Alola, the whole Pokémon world is your Cloyster! Members of this server are allowed a total of four played characters, with at least one required to be canonical.

The server is run by a team of five mods who you can learn more about via the mods page. We cultivate an easygoing and open atmosphere, with member comfort and happiness being our top priority.

All of the links are in the drop down menu under Rowlet, labeled Pokémon! Hovering over each Pokémon will tell you what page they link to!

title: Pokemon alt evolution : Dragonair
body:
I do kinda want an alternative aesthetic evolution for dragonair like so many clamor for, but I want the pokedex entry to make you feel bad.

Dragonair to Dragonite is a shy sea serpent that learns to get over its social anxiety and become basically Barney the Dinosaur crossed with Flipper the dolphin.

An alt evolution should be it getting worse about social interaction.

Idea: “The power of its crystal has increased with evolution. The crushing responsibility of its powers drive it to act withdrawn and aloof.”

@tyrantisterror
